From 2bdc21b4e880fc282b0102e0fbf41b3011afb50d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alexandre Cordeiro <alexandre.s.b.cordeiro@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 21 May 2026 08:31:55 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] Add per-model max-concurrent-requests overrides

Adds a `per_model_max_concurrent` dict on `SchedulerSettings` (and
its passthrough on `SchedulerConfig`). When a key matches the
Scheduler's `model_name` (or its basename) the override value
REPLACES that Scheduler's admission cap; otherwise the global
`max_concurrent_requests` is used as before.

Motivation
==========

oMLX's `EnginePool` creates one Scheduler per model_id. With a
single global `--max-concurrent-requests` the operator must pick a
budget that works for the LARGEST hot model on the GPU; smaller
co-resident models get the same conservative cap even though they
could safely run more parallel requests. On shared Apple Silicon
hardware (M-series base, 16 GB) this matters: e.g. a 3B model can
comfortably serve 4-8 concurrent requests where a co-resident 8B
must stay at 1-2 to avoid the Metal command-buffer watchdog. The
per-model override lets each Scheduler honour its own budget.

Composes with the per-process isolation pattern (one oMLX per model)
the user has on mac-mini today and gives them an in-process
alternative when their GPU has enough headroom for it.

API
===

CLI:
  --per-model-max-concurrent qwen3-8b=4,granite-3b=8

Settings (yaml/json):
  scheduler:
    max_concurrent_requests: 8
    per_model_max_concurrent:
      Qwen3-8B-MLX-4bit: 4
      granite-4.1-3b-4bit: 8

Match order: exact key `model_name`, then `basename(model_name)`.
Falls back to global `max_concurrent_requests` on miss.

Scheduler integration
=====================

The override is applied once in `Scheduler.__init__` immediately
after the SchedulerConfig is copied; the rest of the Scheduler reads
`self.config.max_num_seqs` as before so the admission loop at
`_schedule_waiting` and any per-cap behaviour pick up the override
naturally with no other code changes.

Backward compat
===============

Purely additive. Empty default dict; unset behaviour is identical to
today. `from_dict` coerces values to int so JSON sources that emit
strings still round-trip cleanly.

Tests
=====

`tests/test_per_model_concurrency.py` covers: settings default,
to_dict/from_dict round trip, type coercion, CLI flag parsing
(including malformed pairs and non-integer values), the
`to_scheduler_config` passthrough.
